    Who is the father of Indian art?
    Raja Ravi Varma (18481906)

    Labelled by art historian Geeta Kapur as the father of modern Indian Art, Raja Ravi Varma is best-known for his paintings and prints that exquisitely render Indian subjects using European techniques.

    How can I identify Raja Ravi Varma paintings?
    Raja Ravi Varma is said to have signed his paintings in three types of signature R.V., Ravi Varma and Ravi Varma with the 'V' underlined. Through microscopic examination the strokes, style and signature were examined. In this case the signature was of the third type and the colour dark brown, Mr.1 Mar 2012

    About

    Description

    Raja Ravi Varma was an Indian painter and artist. His works are one of the best examples of the fusion of European academic art with a purely Indian sensibility and iconography. Wikipedia
    Born: 29 April 1848, Kilimanoor
    Died: 2 October 1906 (age 58 years), Attingal
    Children: Kerala Varma, Mahaprabha Amma, Cheria Kochamma, Rama Varma, Uma Amma
    Period: academic art
    Spouse: Pooruruttati Nal Bhageerathi Bayi Thampuratty (m. 18661906)
    Parents: Ezhumavil Neelakanthan Bhattatiripad, Umayamba Thamburatty
    Award: Kaisar-i-Hind Medal
